    "actor_description": "Warmth moves through me the moment I register them-simple, physical, unmistakable. My face softens without permission. My breathing drops lower in my chest. It isn't a rush, and it isn't need. It's steadier than that: the quiet sense that I want to be near, that I'm better oriented when they're in the room. If I reach out, it's not to take-it's to make contact and stay there for a second.",
    "description_text": "{actor}'s features ease as if a tension they didn't notice has let go. Their attention opens-less guarded, more generous. They angle their body toward the person they care about, leaving space closer than necessity requires. When they smile, it arrives slowly and stays.",
